    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-15T10:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-15T10:01:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1102</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tiflis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-15T18:00:00+02:59">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 16, 1.56 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName>Enver Pasha</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d737fn1">Turkish Minister of War.</note> telegraphs to
                    commander in chief here informing him that in view of the Armenian raids and
                    atrocities against Mohammedans he is constrained to resume offensive. Few
                    Armenian troops holding front, scarcely will be able to resist an advance but
                    have been advised to fall back in order, destroying supplies, which I believe
                    form main object of Turkish threat.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SFW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
